  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6766.54 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6765 (-15.2B) and positive gamma at 6780 (+9.2B), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as they're short gamma in this breakout regime. The concentration of negative gamma from 6760-6770 creates a dangerous amplification zone where any momentum will be mechanically reinforced by dealer hedging flows. Watch 6780 as the critical inflection point - a break above triggers dealer selling pressure, while a rejection back into the 6760-6770 cluster could spark violent downside acceleration.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect explosive moves in either direction with dealers adding fuel to the fire.",
